# Class: obo:FLUXO_0000189 (proteomics)

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 obo:FLUXO_0000189 "Proteomics is in the narrow sense (sensu stricto) the application of methods to separate, characterise, identify, and quantify all proteins (the proteome) - or a substantial set of proteins - that are present in a sample.")
AnnotationAssertion(oboInOwl:hasDbXref obo:FLUXO_0000189 "http://edamontology.org/topic_0121")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment obo:FLUXO_0000189 "Proteomics in the broad sense is the science of proteins and peptides on the large scale.")
